There are 481 seats in total for lecture, and 35 * 14 = 490 seats across the sections; in particular, sections 109-114 all have many seats open. I don't see the scenario you describe.

As always, if you can't get into a section, then you can't get into the class. I wouldn't recommend waitlisting for a section where you're that far behind on the waitlist.
